messages.message: cc: @Gaurav Saini / @Yash Aggarwal - can you help take a look ?
Hey, sorry still checking it out. It looks like the ibdoc itself is fine, but there is some failure while its loading in the UI
Let me know when you found something. A lot of them are not working

@Yash Aggarwal I looked into this a little - the `text` field for this particular document from the load_records endpoint is coming back as an empty string, whereas the other docs have that field. That field is what we use to display the text in Refiner. If you open it up in the OCR app, the text shows up fine: https://axa-italia.aws.sandbox.instabase.com/apps/ocr/review-batch/shridhar.kawalkar/my-repo/fs[…]ational+Srl_Klopman_Property_submission.doc.ibmsg= (https://axa-italia.aws.sandbox.instabase.com/apps/ocr/review-batch/shridhar.kawalkar/my-repo/fs/Italy-POV/files/Run/Out/200%20Samples/Property/s2_map_records/-Klopman%20International%20Srl_Klopman_Property_submission.doc.ibmsg?%2Fapps%2Focr%2Freview-batch%2Fshridhar.kawalkar%2Fmy-repo%2Ffs%2FItaly-POV%2Ffiles%2FRun%2FOut%2F200+Samples%2FProperty%2Fs2_map_records%2F-Klopman+International+Srl_Klopman_Property_submission.doc.ibmsg=). We must be using a different way of passing the text in there.

So there's some issue where the text field didn't get saved or isn't being passed back for that ibmsg.
@Jessica Thanks so much for checking it out! Might be an issue with the cpp module :thinking_rotating:… Will update here once I find something…
